==English==
===Etymology===
Latin ''abscessus'' a going away, gathering of humors, [[abscess]], from ''abscessus'', past participle of ''absedere'' to go away; ''ab'', ''abs'' + ''cedere'' to go off, retire. See [[Cede]]
===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-uk-abscess.ogg|Audio (UK)}}

===Noun===
'''abscess''' (''plural'' '''abscesses''')

# {{pathology}} A cavity caused by tissue destruction, usually because of infection, filled with [[pus]] and surrounded by inflammed tissue.

